1. Copyright Notice And License Preservation

The copyright notice, this permission notice, and this full license text must
be included in all copies or substantial portions of the Software, whether in
source form, binary form, documentation, package metadata, or other distributed
materials.

2. Attribution In Public Or Commercial Derivative Works

Any publicly released, distributed, or commercially deployed modified,
extended, forked, or derivative version of the Software must include a clear
acknowledgment of the original Software.

For small, internal, private, or non-distributed forks, attribution is strongly
encouraged but not required. For public releases, distributions, or commercial
deployments, attribution is mandatory.

Acceptable forms include:

- "Based on Smavg 🐲 by Aegis Wizard 🧙‍♂️ (Roman Mataru)"
- "Originally developed from Smavg 🐲 — github.com/aegiswizard/smavg"
- "Derived from Smavg 🐲, authored by Roman Mataru"

This attribution must appear in the LICENSE file, README, About/Credits
section, package metadata, product documentation, or an equivalent location
that is reasonably visible to users or developers. This is a record of origin,
not an endorsement.

3. No Misrepresentation Of Origin

You may not claim authorship of the original Software. Modified versions must
be clearly marked as modified and must not misrepresent their relationship to
the original Software.

COMMERCIAL SCALE ATTRIBUTION CLAUSE

This clause activates only when a commercial product or service using the
Software, or any derivative of the Software, reaches meaningful scale. Below
the thresholds below, this clause creates no additional obligation beyond the
conditions above.

Threshold A — User Scale:
Exceeds 1,000,000 (one million) monthly active users (MAU) in any calendar
month.

Threshold B — Revenue Scale:
Generates more than $500,000 USD (five hundred thousand US dollars) in monthly
gross revenue directly attributable to the product or service incorporating the
Software, or equivalent value in any other currency at prevailing exchange
rates.

Threshold C — Compound:
Simultaneously exceeds 500,000 (five hundred thousand) monthly active users
and $250,000 USD (two hundred and fifty thousand US dollars) in directly
attributable monthly gross revenue.

Attribution Requirement When Triggered:

Prominently display the following attribution:

"Powered by Smavg 🐲 by Aegis Wizard 🧙‍♂️"

For products with a primary user interface, this attribution must be visible
without extra navigation, legible with reasonable contrast, and not hidden,
collapsed, or obscured.

For products without a traditional primary user interface, including but not
limited to CLIs, APIs, SDKs, backend services, daemons, servers, infrastructure
systems, and embedded systems, the attribution must appear in an equivalent
high-visibility location determined in good faith, such as an about/help
screen, command output, public documentation, developer console, service
credits page, API documentation, package page, or administrative interface.

Revenue and user counts are measured on a rolling 30-day basis. Licensees are
responsible for good-faith self-assessment. The copyright holder may request
reasonable compliance documentation with 30 days' written notice.

